The 36-year old made 66 appearances for the South African men's national football team, Bafana Bafana scoring 10 goals over a span of five years, as he made his debut on May 26 against Malawi in the Council of Southern Africa Football Associations (Cosafa) Cup. Sport24 revealed that Modise had plans to call time on his career at the end of the 2018/2019 campaign after playing a lesser role under former South African footballer who is currently the head coach of Cape Town City, Benni McCarthy's Citizens. Modise won two consecutive national sports association, Absa Premiership titles with the South African football club, Mamelodi Sundowns - in the 2013/2014 and 2014/2015 seasons - to go alongside Confederation of African Football (CAF) Champions League trophy as well as winning a host of cups at South African football club, Orlando Pirates. During his time at Pirates, Modise in consecutive seasons won the Premier Soccer League (PSL) Footballer of the Year award - in 2008 and 2009, and was also named South African Football Association (SAFA) Footballer of the Year.

--Sport24--